From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: kSTEP <kstep@kstep.dev>
Date: Sat, 15 Mar 2026 05:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] sched/core: Fix setup_resched_latency_warn_ms() return value

__setup() callbacks expect 1 for success and 0 for failure.
setup_resched_latency_warn_ms() returns 1 when kstrtol() fails to
parse the string, incorrectly telling __setup the parameter was
handled and suppressing the "Unknown kernel command line parameters"
warning. Return 0 on parse failure so the kernel properly reports
the unrecognized parameter.

This is the same anti-pattern that was fixed in setup_preempt_mode()
by commit 9ed20bafc858 ("preempt/dynamic: Fix setup_preempt_mode()
return value").

---
 kernel/sched/core.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/kernel/sched/core.c b/kernel/sched/core.c
index 8d9b02ded5f1..a1b2c3d4e5f6 100644
--- a/kernel/sched/core.c
+++ b/kernel/sched/core.c
@@ -5494,7 +5494,7 @@ static int __init setup_resched_latency_warn_ms(char *str)
 
 	if ((kstrtol(str, 0, &val))) {
 		pr_warn("Unable to set resched_latency_warn_ms\n");
-		return 1;
+		return 0;
 	}
 
 	sysctl_resched_latency_warn_ms = val;
-- 
